SKILL|ascii-art|"ASCII art: pyfiglet, cowsay, boxes, image-to-ascii."
STEP|1|Preview 2-3 fonts and let the user pick their favorite
STEP|2|Short text (1-8 chars) works best with detailed fonts like `doom` or `block`
STEP|3|Long text works better with compact fonts like `small` or `mini`
STEP|4|URL-encode spaces as `+` in the text parameter
STEP|5|The response is plain text ASCII art — no JSON wrapping, ready to display
STEP|6|Font names are case-sensitive; use the fonts endpoint to get exact names
STEP|7|Works from any terminal with curl — no Python or pip needed
STEP|8|Note**: toilet outputs ANSI escape codes for colors — works in terminals but may not render in all contexts (e.g., plain text files, some chat platforms).
STEP|9|URL pattern:** `https://ascii.co.uk/art/{subject}`
STEP|10|Step 1 — Fetch the page:**
STEP|11|Step 2 — Extract art from pre tags:**
STEP|12|Available subjects** (use as URL path):
STEP|13|Animals: `cat`, `dog`, `horse`, `bird`, `fish`, `dragon`, `snake`, `rabbit`, `elephant`, `dolphin`, `butterfly`, `owl`, `wolf`, `bear`, `penguin`, `turtle`
STEP|14|Objects: `car`, `ship`, `airplane`, `rocket`, `guitar`, `computer`, `coffee`, `beer`, `cake`, `house`, `castle`, `sword`, `crown`, `key`
STEP|15|Nature: `tree`, `flower`, `sun`, `moon`, `star`, `mountain`, `ocean`, `rainbow`
STEP|16|Characters: `skull`, `robot`, `angel`, `wizard`, `pirate`, `ninja`, `alien`
STEP|17|Holidays: `christmas`, `halloween`, `valentine`
STEP|18|Tips:**
STEP|19|Preserve artist signatures/initials — important etiquette
STEP|20|Multiple art pieces per page — pick the best one for the user
STEP|21|Works reliably via curl, no JavaScript needed
STEP|22|Box Drawing:** `╔ ╗ ╚ ╝ ║ ═ ╠ ╣ ╦ ╩ ╬ ┌ ┐ └ ┘ │ ─ ├ ┤ ┬ ┴ ┼ ╭ ╮ ╰ ╯`
STEP|23|Block Elements:** `░ ▒ ▓ █ ▄ ▀ ▌ ▐ ▖ ▗ ▘ ▝ ▚ ▞`
STEP|24|Geometric & Symbols:** `◆ ◇ ◈ ● ○ ◉ ■ □ ▲ △ ▼ ▽ ★ ☆ ✦ ✧ ◀ ▶ ◁ ▷ ⬡ ⬢ ⌂`
STEP|25|Max width: 60 characters per line (terminal-safe)
STEP|26|Max height: 15 lines for banners, 25 for scenes
STEP|27|Monospace only: output must render correctly in fixed-width fonts
STEP|28|**Text as a banner** → pyfiglet if installed, otherwise asciified API via curl
STEP|29|**Wrap a message in fun character art** → cowsay
STEP|30|**Add decorative border/frame** → boxes (can combine with pyfiglet/asciified)
STEP|31|**Art of a specific thing** (cat, rocket, dragon) → ascii.co.uk via curl + parsing
STEP|32|**Convert an image to ASCII** → ascii-image-converter or jp2a
STEP|33|**QR code** → qrenco.de via curl
STEP|34|**Weather/moon art** → wttr.in via curl
STEP|35|**Something custom/creative** → LLM generation with Unicode palette
STEP|36|**Any tool not installed** → install it, or fall back to next option
